Bring a large #pot{} of @salted water{} to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @mini cucumber{1}(trimmed and quartered) lengthwise; slice into 1⁄4-inch-thick quarter-moons. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}(halved). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(thinly sliced). Drain and rinse @cannellini beans{1}(drained and rinsed).

Once water is boiling, add @cavatappi pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Drain and rinse under cold water for at least ~{30%seconds}; shake off any excess water.

While pasta cooks, heat a large #dry pan{} over medium-high heat. Add @bacon{4%oz}; cook, turning occasionally and adjusting heat if browning too quickly, until crispy, ~{6-10%minutes}. Transfer to a paper-towel-lined #plate{}. Once cool enough to handle, roughly chop.

In a large #bowl{}, combine drained cavatappi, cucumber, tomatoes, scallions, beans, @mozzarella cheese{1/2%cup}, @creamy balsamic dressing{3%oz}, half the @garlic powder{1%tsp}, half the @dried oregano{1%tsp}, @salt{1/2%tsp}, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} (all the oregano and 1 tsp salt for 4 servings). Toss until well coated. Taste and season with @pepper{} if desired.

Refrigerate until ready to serve.

Place @butter{1%tbsp} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}. Microwave until softened, ~{15-20%seconds}. Stir in remaining garlic powder.

> Use 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

Halve @ciabatta bread{1} lengthwise and toast until golden. Spread with garlic butter.

Cut garlic toast on a diagonal into triangles.

Divide pasta salad between bowls. Serve with garlic toast on the side.

Top pasta salad with bacon.

> Bacon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.